    "I. INTRODUCTIONR OBOT-assisted surgery (RAS) has enormously changed the way many surgeons operate.",
    "Surgical robots can enhance accuracy and dexterity, provide better anatomical access, and minimize invasiveness, surgery time, and the need for revision surgery [1].",
    "With the development of surgical robots and the da Vinci Research Kit (dVRK) [2], along with realistic surgical simulation environments [3]- [5], the automation of surgical sub-tasks such as tissue retraction [6], suturing [7], endoscopic camera control [8], cutting [9], and 1 2 3 4 Deep Reinforcement Learning Agent T=0 T=2s T=4s T=6s T=8s T=10s T=12s T=14sFig.",
